Dialogue: 2,0:00:03.64,0:00:09.88,辉英,,0,0,0,,Get a free trial plus 10% off your first purchase by visiting squarespace.com/primalspace.
Dialogue: 1,0:00:10.54,0:00:19.00,辉中,,0,0,0,,1989年 在太空飞行了12年的旅行者二号成为了首次飞越海王星的探测器
Dialogue: 2,0:00:10.54,0:00:19.00,辉英,,0,0,0,,In 1989, 12 years after leaving Earth, Voyager 2 became the first spacecraft to fly past the mysterious planet of Neptune.
Dialogue: 1,0:00:19.26,0:00:21.72,辉中,,0,0,0,,在当时 人们对这个星球知之甚少
Dialogue: 2,0:00:19.26,0:00:21.72,辉英,,0,0,0,,At this point, very little was known about the planet,
Dialogue: 1,0:00:21.78,0:00:26.44,辉中,,0,0,0,,科学家们只预测到了它的存在 却还未实际观测过
Dialogue: 2,0:00:21.78,0:00:26.44,辉英,,0,0,0,,and scientists had only predicted its existence without actually observing it.
Dialogue: 1,0:00:26.80,0:00:30.68,辉中,,0,0,0,,当旅行者号飞跃的时候 它拍摄了海王星首批照片
Dialogue: 2,0:00:26.80,0:00:30.68,辉英,,0,0,0,,As it flew by, Voyager took the very first images of Neptune,
Dialogue: 1,0:00:30.76,0:00:34.99,辉中,,0,0,0,,向人类展示了一个中央带有巨大深色斑点的光滑蓝色圆球
Dialogue: 2,0:00:30.76,0:00:34.99,辉英,,0,0,0,,showing a smooth blue ball with a giant dark spot right in the center.
Dialogue: 1,0:00:35.31,0:00:38.38,辉中,,0,0,0,,这个深色斑点之后发现是一场大风暴
Dialogue: 2,0:00:35.31,0:00:38.38,辉英,,0,0,0,,This dark spot turned out to be a gigantic storm.
Dialogue: 1,0:00:38.78,0:00:44.05,辉中,,0,0,0,,5年后 海王星再次被哈勃太空望远镜观测到
Dialogue: 2,0:00:38.78,0:00:44.05,辉英,,0,0,0,,5 years later, Neptune was observed again, this time by the Hubble Space telescope.
Dialogue: 1,0:00:44.24,0:00:50.09,辉中,,0,0,0,,当科学家们收到画面时 他们惊讶地发现深色斑点竟然完全消失了
Dialogue: 2,0:00:44.24,0:00:50.09,辉英,,0,0,0,,When scientists received the images, they were stunned to see that the dark spot had completely disappeared.
Dialogue: 1,0:00:50.53,0:00:54.86,辉中,,0,0,0,,他们猜测海王星的大风暴和木星的大红斑类似
Dialogue: 2,0:00:50.53,0:00:54.86,辉英,,0,0,0,,They assumed that Neptune's enormous storm must be similar to Jupiter's Red Spot,
Dialogue: 1,0:00:54.96,0:00:58.05,辉中,,0,0,0,,持续了大约350年
Dialogue: 2,0:00:54.96,0:00:58.05,辉英,,0,0,0,,which has been around for at least 350 years.
Dialogue: 1,0:00:58.46,0:01:02.62,辉中,,0,0,0,,本期视频 我们将了解这些巨大的风暴是如何形成的
Dialogue: 2,0:00:58.46,0:01:02.62,辉英,,0,0,0,,In this video, we're going to look at how these enormous storms form.
Dialogue: 1,0:01:02.72,0:01:08.34,辉中,,0,0,0,,我们还将了解木星的大红斑 以及它为什么可能在我们有生之年消失
Dialogue: 2,0:01:02.72,0:01:08.34,辉英,,0,0,0,,We're also going to look at Jupiter's Great Red Spot and why it might disappear in our lifetime.
Dialogue: 1,0:01:08.99,0:01:14.05,辉中,,0,0,0,,有记载的地球上最大的风暴是1994年的飓风“约翰”
Dialogue: 2,0:01:08.99,0:01:14.05,辉英,,0,0,0,,The longest storm ever recorded on Earth was Hurricane John in 1994.
Dialogue: 1,0:01:14.24,0:01:21.20,辉中,,0,0,0,,它持续31天 路径总长超过13000公里 横跨太平洋
Dialogue: 2,0:01:14.24,0:01:21.20,辉英,,0,0,0,,It lasted 31 days and travelled over 13,000 kilometres as it wandered across the Pacific Ocean.
Dialogue: 1,0:01:21.36,0:01:24.44,辉中,,0,0,0,,尽管它是地球上非常大的风暴
Dialogue: 2,0:01:21.36,0:01:24.44,辉英,,0,0,0,,Although this is a monumental storm by Earth standards,
Dialogue: 1,0:01:24.50,0:01:31.55,辉中,,0,0,0,,但和海王星 木星上持续时间几个月几年甚至几世纪的风暴相比还是图样
Dialogue: 2,0:01:24.50,0:01:31.55,辉英,,0,0,0,,it's nothing compared to the storms on Neptune and Jupiter, which can last for months, years, or even centuries.
Dialogue: 1,0:01:31.98,0:01:36.83,辉中,,0,0,0,,在地球上 飓风起源于海上蒸发的暖湿水汽
Dialogue: 2,0:01:31.98,0:01:36.83,辉英,,0,0,0,,On Earth, the power of a hurricane comes from warm vapour evaporating from the sea.
Dialogue: 1,0:01:36.90,0:01:40.38,辉中,,0,0,0,,形成密集的云后 会向空气中释放热量
Dialogue: 2,0:01:36.90,0:01:40.38,辉英,,0,0,0,,This forms dense clouds which release heat into the air.
Dialogue: 1,0:01:40.65,0:01:43.63,辉中,,0,0,0,,在特定条件下 这会产生一个低压区域
Dialogue: 2,0:01:40.65,0:01:43.63,辉英,,0,0,0,,In the right conditions, this creates an area of low pressure
Dialogue: 1,0:01:43.63,0:01:47.39,辉中,,0,0,0,,暖空气上升 冷空气被吸入底部
Dialogue: 2,0:01:43.63,0:01:47.39,辉英,,0,0,0,,with warm air rising and cooler air being sucked in at the bottom.
Dialogue: 1,0:01:47.74,0:01:51.23,辉中,,0,0,0,,而地球在赤道附近的自转线速度更大
Dialogue: 2,0:01:47.74,0:01:51.23,辉英,,0,0,0,,Since the Earth spins at a higher velocity closer to the equator,
Dialogue: 1,0:01:51.23,0:01:56.74,辉中,,0,0,0,,流向低压区的风开始偏转 让飓风产生旋转
Dialogue: 2,0:01:51.23,0:01:56.74,辉英,,0,0,0,,winds travelling towards the area of low pressure begin to curve which causes the hurricane to spin.
Dialogue: 1,0:01:56.90,0:02:00.27,辉中,,0,0,0,,飓风通常会在遇到陆地后开始消散
Dialogue: 2,0:01:56.90,0:02:00.27,辉英,,0,0,0,,A hurricane will usually start to dissipate once it reaches land,
Dialogue: 1,0:02:00.27,0:02:04.49,辉中,,0,0,0,,因为没有暖湿水汽的供给 也就无法让它继续旋转
Dialogue: 2,0:02:00.27,0:02:04.49,辉英,,0,0,0,,where it no longer receives the warm vapour it needs to keep the cycle going.
Dialogue: 1,0:02:04.98,0:02:10.46,辉中,,0,0,0,,与地球上的典型的气旋不同 木星的大红斑是反气旋
Dialogue: 2,0:02:04.98,0:02:10.46,辉英,,0,0,0,,Unlike typical cyclones on Earth, the Great Red Spot on Jupiter is an anticyclone
Dialogue: 1,0:02:10.46,0:02:13.36,辉中,,0,0,0,,它产生于高压区
Dialogue: 2,0:02:10.46,0:02:13.36,辉英,,0,0,0,,which forms around an area of high pressure.
Dialogue: 1,0:02:13.44,0:02:16.93,辉中,,0,0,0,,大红斑的动力来源于两侧的气流
Dialogue: 2,0:02:13.44,0:02:16.93,辉英,,0,0,0,,The red spot is powered by two jet streams on either side
Dialogue: 1,0:02:16.93,0:02:21.30,辉中,,0,0,0,,让大红斑持续旋转 又让它无法沿着星球到处移动
Dialogue: 2,0:02:16.93,0:02:21.30,辉英,,0,0,0,,which give the storm a constant spin but stop it from moving across the planet.
Dialogue: 1,0:02:21.70,0:02:24.83,辉中,,0,0,0,,地球上的风暴动力来自于太阳给地球的热量
Dialogue: 2,0:02:21.70,0:02:24.83,辉英,,0,0,0,,While a storm on Earth is powered by the heat from the sun,
Dialogue: 1,0:02:24.83,0:02:31.07,辉中,,0,0,0,,木星上的风暴动力则来自于它自身高达27700摄氏度的金属内核
Dialogue: 2,0:02:24.83,0:02:31.07,辉英,,0,0,0,,a storm on Jupiter is powered by the heat from its metallic core, which could be as hot as 50,000 degrees.
Dialogue: 1,0:02:31.42,0:02:34.56,辉中,,0,0,0,,上升的热流和快速移动的云
Dialogue: 2,0:02:31.42,0:02:34.56,辉英,,0,0,0,,The combination of rising heat and fast moving clouds
Dialogue: 1,0:02:34.56,0:02:39.69,辉中,,0,0,0,,让大红斑的边缘风速可以高达每小时680公里
Dialogue: 2,0:02:34.56,0:02:39.69,辉英,,0,0,0,,are what push the Great Red Spot around with speeds of up to 680 km/h.
Dialogue: 1,0:02:40.28,0:02:46.35,辉中,,0,0,0,,且木星是气态行星 它没有所谓的海洋或者陆地这种“屏障”
Dialogue: 2,0:02:40.28,0:02:46.35,辉英,,0,0,0,,Since Jupiter is a gas giant, it doesn't have the contrast of ocean and land to act as a barrier.
Dialogue: 1,0:02:46.59,0:02:52.12,辉中,,0,0,0,,海王星的风暴则起因于类似的 大气深处的高压区
Dialogue: 2,0:02:46.59,0:02:52.12,辉英,,0,0,0,,The storms on Neptune form around a similar region of high pressure, deep in the atmosphere.
Dialogue: 1,0:02:52.30,0:02:56.38,辉中,,0,0,0,,深色斑点形成前通常能在高压区见到白色的甲烷云
Dialogue: 2,0:02:52.30,0:02:56.38,辉英,,0,0,0,,White clouds of methane are commonly seen in regions of high pressure
Dialogue: 1,0:02:56.38,0:02:58.57,辉中,,0,0,0,,深色斑点形成前通常能在高压区见到白色的甲烷云
Dialogue: 2,0:02:56.38,0:02:58.57,辉英,,0,0,0,,just before a dark spot forms.
Dialogue: 1,0:02:58.96,0:03:01.96,辉中,,0,0,0,,当海王星上的风暴逐渐成长为完全体
Dialogue: 2,0:02:58.96,0:03:01.96,辉英,,0,0,0,,Once a storm on Neptune has grown to its full size,
Dialogue: 1,0:03:01.96,0:03:09.22,辉中,,0,0,0,,边缘风速可以达到每小时2100公里 是全太阳系最大的风
Dialogue: 2,0:03:01.96,0:03:09.22,辉英,,0,0,0,,the winds at the edge of the storm can be travelling up to 2,100km/h, the fastest in our solar system.
Dialogue: 1,0:03:09.42,0:03:13.64,辉中,,0,0,0,,与木星大红斑不同的是 海王星上的风暴可以满星球到处跑
Dialogue: 2,0:03:09.42,0:03:13.64,辉英,,0,0,0,,Unlike Jupiter's Red Spot, the storms on Neptune get pushed around the planet
Dialogue: 1,0:03:13.64,0:03:16.25,辉中,,0,0,0,,并会被侧风吹散分解
Dialogue: 2,0:03:13.64,0:03:16.25,辉英,,0,0,0,,where they get shredded by powerful crosswinds.
Dialogue: 1,0:03:16.48,0:03:22.01,辉中,,0,0,0,,因此 海王星上各地的风暴通常持续几个月到几年不等
Dialogue: 2,0:03:16.48,0:03:22.01,辉英,,0,0,0,,Because of this, storms on Neptune typically last anywhere from a few months to a few years.
Dialogue: 1,0:03:22.36,0:03:27.17,辉中,,0,0,0,,因为地球上观测木星更容易 人类观测大红斑的历史
Dialogue: 2,0:03:22.36,0:03:27.17,辉英,,0,0,0,,Since Jupiter is much easier to see from Earth, our observations of the red spot go back
Dialogue: 1,0:03:27.17,0:03:33.00,辉中,,0,0,0,,也能追溯到1665年天文学家乔凡尼·多美尼科·卡西尼对其的首次观测
Dialogue: 2,0:03:27.17,0:03:33.00,辉英,,0,0,0,,to 1665 when Astronomer Gian Domenico Cassini first discovered the giant storm.
Dialogue: 1,0:03:33.36,0:03:38.00,辉中,,0,0,0,,从那以后 人类能够一直观测它 并见证它的变化
Dialogue: 2,0:03:33.36,0:03:38.00,辉英,,0,0,0,,Since then, we have been able to observe the red spot and watch it evolve over time.
Dialogue: 1,0:03:38.52,0:03:43.65,辉中,,0,0,0,,然而 这些观测发现这场象征木星标志的风暴可能快要结束了
Dialogue: 2,0:03:38.52,0:03:43.65,辉英,,0,0,0,,However, these observations have shown that the end may be near for this iconic storm.
Dialogue: 1,0:03:44.20,0:03:51.98,辉中,,0,0,0,,在19世纪的观测中 大红斑长40000公里 高14000公里
Dialogue: 2,0:03:44.20,0:03:51.98,辉英,,0,0,0,,When it was observed in the 19th century, the Great Red Spot was 40,000km long and 14,000km tall.
Dialogue: 1,0:03:52.14,0:03:56.03,辉中,,0,0,0,,当时 它能装下两到三个地球
Dialogue: 2,0:03:52.14,0:03:56.03,辉英,,0,0,0,,At that point, it could have swallowed 2 or 3 earths whole.
Dialogue: 1,0:03:56.44,0:04:01.80,辉中,,0,0,0,,但旅行者一号在70年代末飞越的时候 大红斑却只有几乎一半大小
Dialogue: 2,0:03:56.44,0:04:01.80,辉英,,0,0,0,,But by the time Voyager 1 flew past in the late 70s, it was almost half the size.
Dialogue: 1,0:04:02.12,0:04:09.18,辉中,,0,0,0,,哈勃最近的观测发现大红斑在以每年1000公里的速度缩小
Dialogue: 2,0:04:02.12,0:04:09.18,辉英,,0,0,0,,Recent observations by the Hubble telescope show that the storm is currently shrinking at about 1000km per year,
Dialogue: 1,0:04:09.18,0:04:12.90,辉中,,0,0,0,,这意味着它可能会在2030年彻底消失
Dialogue: 2,0:04:09.18,0:04:12.90,辉英,,0,0,0,,meaning it could completely disappear by the 2030's.
Dialogue: 1,0:04:13.41,0:04:20.30,辉中,,0,0,0,,除了在缩小 大红斑主体看上去还在被分解成更小的气流 颜色也在变深
Dialogue: 2,0:04:13.41,0:04:20.30,辉英,,0,0,0,,As well as losing size, the main red spot seems to be breaking off into smaller streams and darkening in color.
Dialogue: 1,0:04:20.58,0:04:24.30,辉中,,0,0,0,,科学家们认为风暴正在接近木星的高层大气
Dialogue: 2,0:04:20.58,0:04:24.30,辉英,,0,0,0,,Scientists believe that since the storm is reaching higher into the atmosphere,
Dialogue: 1,0:04:24.30,0:04:29.96,辉中,,0,0,0,,大红斑的顶部会受到更多紫外线的照射 让其中的化学物质颜色变深
Dialogue: 2,0:04:24.30,0:04:29.96,辉英,,0,0,0,,the top of the red spot is exposed to more UV light which darkens the color of the chemicals.
Dialogue: 1,0:04:30.20,0:04:37.47,辉中,,0,0,0,,但这和地球上的天气预报一样 这些巨大风暴背后还有很多人类未解之谜
Dialogue: 2,0:04:30.20,0:04:37.47,辉英,,0,0,0,,But, like predicting the weather here on Earth, there is still so much that we don't know about these gigantic storms.
Dialogue: 1,0:04:37.85,0:04:40.38,辉中,,0,0,0,,当人类首次发现海王星的深色斑点时
Dialogue: 2,0:04:37.85,0:04:40.38,辉英,,0,0,0,,When Neptune's Dark Spot was first discovered,
Dialogue: 1,0:04:40.38,0:04:44.61,辉中,,0,0,0,,科学家们以为它和木星的大红斑一样存在了几个世纪
Dialogue: 2,0:04:40.38,0:04:44.61,辉英,,0,0,0,,scientists thought that it had been around for centuries just like Jupiter's storm.
Dialogue: 1,0:04:44.90,0:04:48.68,辉中,,0,0,0,,大红斑的温度也比我们预料的要高
Dialogue: 2,0:04:44.90,0:04:48.68,辉英,,0,0,0,,The Great Red Spot is also far hotter than we initially imagined,
Dialogue: 1,0:04:48.68,0:04:52.51,辉中,,0,0,0,,它上部的大气温度超过1300度
Dialogue: 2,0:04:48.68,0:04:52.51,辉英,,0,0,0,,with parts of it's upper atmosphere exceeding 1300 degrees.
Dialogue: 1,0:04:52.90,0:04:56.34,辉中,,0,0,0,,即使我们观测的技术在不断进步
Dialogue: 2,0:04:52.90,0:04:56.34,辉英,,0,0,0,,Even with the increases in our observational technology,
Dialogue: 1,0:04:56.34,0:05:03.50,辉中,,0,0,0,,这些巨大 未知的星球仍有无数知识等待我们去探寻
Dialogue: 2,0:04:56.34,0:05:03.50,辉英,,0,0,0,,there is still so much knowledge trapped inside the boundaries of these giant, mysterious planets, waiting to be discovered.
Dialogue: 1,0:05:03.50,0:05:08.04,辉中,,0,0,0,,虽然我们可能将要失去太阳系最有象征意义的符号
Dialogue: 2,0:05:03.50,0:05:08.04,辉英,,0,0,0,,So although we might be losing one of the most iconic features of our solar system,
Dialogue: 1,0:05:08.08,0:05:15.05,辉中,,0,0,0,,但我们对它有限的观测却能让我们更好的理解太阳系内的自然法则
Dialogue: 2,0:05:08.08,0:05:15.05,辉英,,0,0,0,,the observations we make of it will give us a better understanding of how nature operates throughout our solar system.
Dialogue: 1,0:05:15.56,0:05:19.55,辉中,,0,0,0,,在Squarespace上创建网站简直太容易了
Dialogue: 2,0:05:15.56,0:05:19.55,辉英,,0,0,0,,Creating a website for your business with Squarespace is incredibly easy.
Dialogue: 1,0:05:19.88,0:05:21.79,辉中,,0,0,0,,如果你是搞艺术或者搞摄影的
Dialogue: 2,0:05:19.88,0:05:21.79,辉英,,0,0,0,,If you are an artist or a photographer,
Dialogue: 1,0:05:21.79,0:05:26.54,辉中,,0,0,0,,有一个专门的网站供人们浏览 购买作品是很有必要的
